From: guillaume <guillaume.chaye@zeetim.com>
Subject: [PATCH] httpd: retire ASUS web UI by default on standalone AP (nvram gtbe98_httpd)

Phase 2 (rc-drain): the open webui (go/lighttpd under /usr/br, rail S29/S30br-webui)
owns the management UI. Gate the ASUS httpd starter AND its watchdog respawn on a new
unused nvram flag gtbe98_httpd (default off, 0024/0027/0028 early-return model).

CRITICAL flash-wear hazard fixed at source: httpd_check() in rc/watchdog.c, when the
httpd binary is missing, runs nvram_set("last_httpd_handle_request",...) +
nvram_set(...fromapp...) + nvram_commit() EVERY watchdog period (watchdog.c:8018-8020).
Naive removal of the ASUS UI binary (rootfs-remove) without this gate would grind NAND
flash on every watchdog tick. The gate sits ABOVE that block so the respawn/commit path
is never entered. Re-enable: nvram set gtbe98_httpd=1 ; nvram commit.
See gt-be98-docs/device/plans/patch-0033-0034-notes.md (br-0047/br-0048 webui slices).
---
diff --git a/release/src/router/rc/services.c b/release/src/router/rc/services.c
--- a/release/src/router/rc/services.c
+++ b/release/src/router/rc/services.c
@@ -7280,6 +7280,14 @@
 	char *httpd_dir;
 #endif
 
+	/* Fork GT-BE98 : httpd (UI web ASUS, :80) desactive par defaut -- le webui
+	 * (go/lighttpd sous /usr/br, rail S29) possede l'interface d'administration.
+	 * Sur AP autonome rc n'a pas besoin de l'UI ASUS. Garde placee AVANT le relais
+	 * notify_rc pour ne pas non plus re-declencher start_httpd via le chemin PID1.
+	 * Reactiver : nvram set gtbe98_httpd=1 ; nvram commit. */
+	if (!nvram_get_int("gtbe98_httpd"))
+		return;
+
 	if (getpid() != 1) {
 		notify_rc("start_httpd");
 		return;
diff --git a/release/src/router/rc/watchdog.c b/release/src/router/rc/watchdog.c
--- a/release/src/router/rc/watchdog.c
+++ b/release/src/router/rc/watchdog.c
@@ -7998,6 +7998,14 @@
 
 void httpd_check()
 {
+	/* Fork GT-BE98 : ne pas relancer httpd s'il est desactive (cf. start_httpd).
+	 * CRITIQUE : sans cette garde, quand le binaire httpd est absent ce check
+	 * fait nvram_set()+nvram_commit() (lignes "last_httpd_handle_request") A CHAQUE
+	 * periode de watchdog -> ecriture NAND repetee (usure flash). La garde DOIT
+	 * rester au-dessus de ce bloc. Reactiver : nvram set gtbe98_httpd=1 ; nvram commit. */
+	if (!nvram_get_int("gtbe98_httpd"))
+		return;
+
 	if (nvram_get_int("wait_httpd")) {
 		nvram_set_int("wait_httpd", 0);
 		return;
